com.vaadin.event.MethodEventSource, com.vaadin.terminal.Paintable, com.vaadin.terminal.Sizeable, com.vaadin.terminal.VariableOwner, com.vaadin.ui.Component, com.vaadin.ui.ComponentContainer, TabNavigator.ViewChangeListener, java.io.Serializable, java.util.EventListener
public class OpenDemocracyVotingEntityManagerView
extends com.vaadin.ui.CustomComponent
implements TabNavigator.ViewChangeListener

Entity manager view that by default automatically discovers all entity views (classes with the RooVaadinEntityView annotation) and lets the user choose one of them to display. An entity view must implement the Navigator.View interface to be automatically added to the view list. Other views can be registered by calling navigator.addView() and added to the sidebar menu by adding a corresponding SidebarItem to menuItems and viewList. This class is designed to be compatible with the Vaadin Visual Editor. All methods and fields not marked with the AutoGenerated annotation can be modified freely. If you are planning to use the visual editor, do not touch the methods marked with the AutoGenerated annotation - they will be removed and re-generated when saving the class from the visual editor. Instead, add any custom code to methods called from the constructor after the initial view construction. If you will not use the Vaadin Visual Editor to edit this class, all the AutoGenerated annotations can be removed.
